name: Greenyard Restaurant & Bar

reviews.review_text:
Good food but price are bit high..if place is crowded then your order will  get delayed for suree

We tried their almost all chicken dishes

1.chicken muglai
2.chicken kholapuri
3.pepper chicken is must try
4.crispy chicken
5.chicken fried rice
6.chicken pakora
7.chicken manchao soup
8.masala papad
9.green salad
10.chapati
11.lime soda

It was very disappointed the day we went tandoori counter was not available

This is located near Basilica church and Museum. Food tasted good. Chicken tikka was good. But Service was bad because they served expired beer. Atmosphere is below average as only some tourists or locals might come here. This is not a very happening place like one expects in Goa.

A guest actually recommended this place for goan food. Yesterday we went there for lunch.
The restaurant is right outside St. Cajetan Church.
We ordered the fish thali with king fish for 1 and pomfret for the other.
It took a little while for the food to arrive. It was hot, freshly prepared and tasty. They also serve green vegetables. Yesterday it was bhendi. Also the tisrio was amazing. The Masala was just right. Not too spicy.
I would definitely recommend this place for visitors who come to Old Goa.

description:
### Discovering Culinary Delights at Greenyard Restaurant & Bar

Tucked away in the quaint setting of Goa Velha, just a stone's throw from the iconic Basilica of Bom Jesus, Greenyard Restaurant & Bar has garnered a solid rating of 4.0 from a remarkable 796 reviewers. Known for its Goan charm, delectable seafood, and vibrant local culture, this restaurant is a popular stop for both locals and tourists alike. With frequent references to its "Goan" cuisine (39 mentions), "seafood" delights (27 mentions), and proximity to the church (21 mentions), the establishment is engulfed in both history and culinary experience.

### The Ambiance: A Blend of Culture and Comfort

Upon entering Greenyard, guests are greeted by a cozy yet unpretentious atmosphere, reflective of the local culture. The dining area features traditional Goan décor, infused with warm lighting that creates a welcoming space for conversation and relaxation. The layout appears to maintain an inviting yet casual vibe, suitable for family gatherings or informal meals with friends, though some reviews suggest it may not be the bustling hotspot one might expect in Goa. From the photos, we can discern an inviting environment adorned with local artwork, which adds to the charm of this hidden gem.

### A Menu of Delights

Greenyard shines when it comes to its culinary offerings, capturing the essence of Goan flavors with a diverse selection. Signature dishes highlighted by diners include the famed **fish thali**, featuring king fish and pomfret, praised for its freshness and skillful preparation. Reviewers have also echoed sentiments for the chicken specialties, including the spicy **chicken kholapuri** and the succulent **pepper chicken**, which comes highly recommended. The visual appeal of the dishes, as seen in the provided images, showcases vibrant colors and meticulous presentation, promising an enjoyable feast for the eyes as well as the palate.

Despite some critiques regarding the availability and price of certain items—like the absence of the tandoori counter on busy days—most patrons seem satisfied with the quality of food served. The menu caters to various dietary preferences, including vegetarian options such as masala papad and green salads.

### Service and Customer Experience

Customer experiences at Greenyard reveal a mix of sentiments, particularly regarding service. While many diners have praised the food quality, there are concerns about delays during peak hours and issues with staff efficiency. Notably, one reviewer mentioned a mishap with serving expired beer, which put a damper on the dining experience. Despite these hiccups, the overall friendliness of the staff appears to shine through, with many guests noting their willingness to assist. Reservations are not mentioned, signaling that walk-ins may be welcome, though arriving early could help avoid longer waits during meal times.

### Popularity and Review Highlights

Greenyard has carved a niche within the culinary landscape of Goa, with a good mix of feedback that paints a picture of its strengths and areas for improvement. Many reviews highlight the authenticity of Goan cuisine, and several customers have recommended the restaurant as a must-visit spot when in Old Goa. As captured in the reviews, the combination of good food and a quaint location offers visitors a unique taste of local culture, despite the occasional service misstep.

### Bringing It All Together

With a picturesque backdrop of Goa Velha's historic sites, Greenyard Restaurant & Bar serves as a testament to the region's culinary offerings. As evidenced by customer photos, the dishes are not only flavorful but beautifully presented, making each meal a noteworthy experience. Whether you're indulging in the much-loved seafood thali or enjoying a casual evening out with their varied chicken dishes, Greenyard promises a taste of Goa's rich heritage, albeit with a few bumps along the way. For anyone looking to explore the flavors of this coastal paradise, Greenyard stands as a solid choice to consider.
